  "body": "I ran `helm dependency update` while `helm serve` wasn't running. helm decided the best thing to do was delete all the subcharts, even though it could not download new versions! Afterwards the 'charts' folder was empty.\r\n\r\nI would have expect either:\r\n- no subcharts would be updated if a download error occured, or \r\n- only charts for which a replacement had been downloaded would be deleted\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ helm dependency update drupal-efs\r\nHang tight while we grab the latest from your chart repositories...\r\n...Unable to get an update from the \"local\" chart repository (http://127.0.0.1:8879/charts):\r\n\tGet http://127.0.0.1:8879/charts/index.yaml: dial tcp 127.0.0.1:8879: getsockopt: connection refused\r\n...Successfully got an update from the \"stable\" chart repository\r\nUpdate Complete. \u2388Happy Helming!\u2388\r\nDeleting outdated charts\r\nSaving 3 charts\r\nDownloading mysql-efs from repo http://127.0.0.1:8879/charts\r\nError: could not download http://127.0.0.1:8879/charts/mysql-efs-0.1.8.tgz: Get http://127.0.0.1:8879/charts/mysql-efs-0.1.8.tgz: dial tcp 127.0.0.1:8879: getsockopt: connection refused\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\nClient: &version.Version{SemVer:\"v2.5.1\", GitCommit:\"7cf31e8d9a026287041bae077b09165be247ae66\", GitTreeState:\"clean\"}\r\n```\r\n",
